                    <div class="right_img">
                        <%= image_tag("wles_entrance.png", alt: "WLES Entrance") %>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="text_container flex-1">
                    <h2 class="text-black">The funds will be used for:</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mb-2">
                            HVAC & Lighting Systems
                            <ul>
                                <li>Install a new district-wide HVAC control system. Current systems are only partially working.</li>
                                <li>Replace and repair select univents, the main source of heating/cooling/ventilation in classrooms.</li>
                                <li>Upgrade to energy-efficient lighting.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="mb-2">
                            Safety & Security Enhancements
                            <ul>
                                <li>Reconfigure the Elementary School entrance to improve security.</li>
                                <li>Improve exterior entrance security at all campuses.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="mb-2">
                            Parking Lots & Curbs
                            <ul>
                                <li>Replace parking lots, sidewalks, and curbing at Whitmore Lake Elementary School and Main Street Campus</li>
                                <li>Repair select areas at Whitmore Lake Middle & High School</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="mb-2">
                            Ongoing Repairs & Buses
                            <ul>
                                <li>Address other critical issues as they arise, based on our district-wide Facility Assessment.</li>
                                <li>Purchase new buses as needed.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mb-0 ff-opb">What is the difference between a Bond and a Sinking Fund?</p>
            <p>Unlike a bond, which is a large loan the district can use right away to make a significantly positive impact quickly, a Sinking Fund provides a set amount of revenue each year to chip away at the list slowly. It is more affordable for the community since there are no interest payments.</p>
            <p class="mb-0 ff-opb">What will happen to the current Sinking Fund?</p>
            <p>The current 0.9458 mil sinking fund is essential to maintaining the district technology replacement plan and is earmarked to make necessary facility repairs not included in the scope of work for the 2024 Sinking Fund. It will be up for renewal in 2027.</p>
            <p class="mb-0 ff-opb">WLPS Fiscal Stability & Responsibility</p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-center mb-5">
                <a href="/transparency-reporting" class = "text-white">
                    <button class="btn_normal">Annual Budget Reports</button>
                </a>
            </div>
            <p class="mb-0">We have efficiently leveraged our previous Sinking Fund to meet student and staff technology needs and make essential facility repairs. With this new Sinking Fund, we would continue to invest strategically in our school's infrastructure, to meet our goal of providing our students and staff, minimally, with learning environments that are consistently warm, safe, and dry.</p>
            <div class="text-center py-4_5">
                <%= image_tag("5_year_avg.png", alt: "5-Year Projection Average", class: "origin w-md-full") %>
            </div>
            <p class="text-center">WLPS has consistently experienced an increase in enrollment in early childhood programs (141% increase) and in elementary-aged students (15% increase) since Fall 2021. An independent enrollment projection estimates a 20% increase in K-12 over the next 5 years. To better serve our current students and to prepare for future growth, we need to address key issues now.</p>
            <div class="bond_btns_2">
                <a href="https://assets-whitmore-lake.s3.amazonaws.com/website_pdfs/wlps_enrollment_statistics_projections_flyer%20%282%29.pdf" class = "text-white" target="_blank">
                    <button class="rule_btn_2 primary-bg py-3 text-white">View Enrollment Projections</button>
                </a>
                <a href="/bond-updates" class = "text-white">
                    <button class="rule_btn_2 primary-bg py-3 text-white">Sinking Fund & Recreation Millage Updates</button>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

