            <p class="text-center">If the $12 million Sinking Fund does not pass, our district will face significant challenges in maintaining our facilities while also maintaining high-quality staff and educational programming. The money needs to come from somewhere. If this funding source is not approved, our school community should expect cuts to our general fund budget to pay for repairs. This could mean staff cuts, lower wages, and program cuts. We will be forced to pit providing a warm, safe, and dry learning environment for our students against our goals of employing and retaining high-quality staff and expanding program opportunities.</p>
